>Here is a simple proposal for extending DES to a 112 bit key which is 
>also easy to implement based on the existing DES implementations 
>(important for speed). 
For those who might be interested, there's an implementation of this 
that I hacked up in a spare hour based on Eric Young's LIBDES 
available for anon ftp from 
wimsey.bc.ca in 
/pub/crypto/software/dist/US_or_Canada_only_XXXXXXXX/DES/des2-1.1.1-tar.gz

(U.S. and Canadian persons only, please).

Speed on a 486/DX33 (8K cache) seems to be a little slower than the
IDEA implementation in PGP.

Time for 200000 single block ecb encryptions and one key setup
IDEA  13.9s
DES2  16.4s (DES2 for lack of a better name)

(compiled with gcc 2.5.8, -O2)

Mark
